{
  "texts": [
    "In this work, we use the ORMASK column to identify low-quality data since it is more strict than the ANDMASK column.",
    "If a MRS spectrum has bad pixels (flux values equal to or less than zero) or low-quality pixels (indicated by ORMASK) in the wavelength bands of the Hα line utilized in this work, the spectrum is removed from our sample.",
    "The radial velocity parameter of a MRS spectrum is required to transform the wavelengths of the spectrum to the values in the rest frame.",
    "The LAMOST MRS Parameter Catalog provides radial velocity parameters rv r0 and rv b0 for the red band and blue band of MRS, respectively.",
    "Since the Hα line is contained in the red band of MRS, we use rv r0 and its uncertainty (rv r0 err) in the analysis of this work, and the spectra with missing rv r0 or rv r0 err values are removed from our sample."
  ]
}